Rudzani Matshili Acting Chief of Metro Police, Jenny Malan, congratulated the Tshwane Metro Police (TMPD) members who successfully completed the crowd management course. The officers underwent a one month full training on crowd management in Thabazimbi, Limpopo, during September. They were trained on crowd control during protests, gatherings, sports and recreation. During an award ceremony where they were being honoured this morning, Malan said she was proud of the police officers. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window.  “As the chief, I'm very proud that you fully committed yourselves to successfully completing this crowd management course and you will be there for the community that you serve,” she said. The initiative came as a call for all law enforcement agencies to undergo training on crowd control after the Marikana incident. In attendance were the MMC of community safety Alderman Kissoonduth, city manager Moeketsi Mosola and executive mayor Solly Msimanga. The police officers were handed certificates by Msimanga and other officials. Music was played by the TMPD Ceremonial Band and Choir through out the ceremony.